parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and rear-end collisions, posing a significant safety risk to the rider and other road users.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
often when decelerating
downshifting
or engaging the clutch
resulting in loss of power and control. This can occur at various speeds
including low speeds
and may be accompanied by the loss of turn signals and speed control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the motorcycle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The clutch basket shatters
causing massive damage to the engine
the motorcycle stalls or loses power
especially when slowing down or coming to a stop with the clutch pulled in
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear final drive can cause the motorcycle to become unstable, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Bearings in the rear wheel final drive fail
oil seal failure causes the rear tire and brake disk to be coated with oil
the motorcycle becomes unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the motorcycle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ignition coil fails
the starter relay fails
the combination switch fails
the motorcycle fails to start
the horn and high beam headlights do not operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An incorrect fuel economy reading can lead to inaccurate fuel level estimates, causing drivers to run out of fuel unexpectedly, which can result in accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The fuel economy meter displays an incorrect reading
showing higher miles per gallon than the actual fuel efficiency
leading to inaccurate fuel level estimates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power can cause the motorcycle to stall, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially when crossing intersections or navigating heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls when the clutch is disengaged
resulting in a sudden loss of power
often occurring randomly or when slowing down with the clutch pulled in.
